      "side": 1,
      "message": "test attributes says:\n\"n automated testing, tests to run are usually selected by groups. This means that a test will not run in automated testing if it belongs to no group.\"\n\nIt is not clear to me that this disables test as it says:\n- test are run usually by group. Meaning there are some other ways tests are run\n- it is enough to remove \"group:*\" attribute but leave e.g. \"informational\" to disable the test. Is that the case?\n\nI am thinking what about having actually explicit attribute to disable tests? Like\ngroup:disabled ?",
      "parentUuid": "7787edb7_de6c0a72",
      "revId": "3aaad7b7aca4d637629c90330c701ca5b17184a7",
